    "summary": "\u201cA teacher, from birth till death, for the whole life, is a master who figures the life. No\nother being might be equal to such an outstanding creature who guides its nation and\nhuman beings in their destiny, who enriches their morals, character and knowledge.\u201d\n\n\u201cMetals become purified in the hands of the teacher, transformed into solid gold\nand bright silver. The rawest and the most worthless things become like diamonds\nin the mysterious hands of a teacher. No manufacturer can do a work as fast and\nsystematically as a teacher does. To transmit all his\\her emotions to hundreds of people\nbefore him\\her in an instant and to become like a second entity in their own entities are\nnot possible for anybody except teachers.\u201d\n\nAs an English teacher I persevere at:\n\n\u2022 Teaching the truth,\n\u2022 Encouraging my students think truly,\n\u2022 Exciting the hearts of my students in order that they reach the \u201cknowledge\u201d truly,\n\u2022 Eliminating the barriers and darkness before my students in order that they are\nenlightened.\n\u2022 Keeping up with students\u2019 life out of school,\n\u2022 Carrying the teaching and learning away from the classroom,\n\u2022 Having bonds with my students.\n\nMy primary goal as a teacher is to stimulate young learners to internalize love,\npeace, tolerance, dialogue, global citizenship, so that they piece together the units\nof society and they arouse humanistic, ethical, moral dynamics of both the nation in\nwhich they live and the universe. This comes true only through having bonds with\nmy learners, therefore as a teacher, I must have at my students\u2019 fingerprints. This\nis because teachers are leaders with an authority, and leaders know their people\nwell. A leader knows the expectations and fears of his group, talents and failings of\nhis individuals. \n\nAdditionally, I have recently been mingling with internationally focused\ncurriculum such as Cambridge, Pearson Edexcel and IB.Thus, I have acquired new\nand better perspectives, in other words I have been improving my key language and\nliterature teaching strategies such as:\n\n\u2022 `Active Learning` with which I conduct strategies focusing on student centered\nactivities that allow students to construct knowledge and meaning\n\u2022 `Critical Thinking` with which I often apply to the strategies for promoting\nstudents\u2019 critical thinking skills, such as evaluating, comparing and questioning.\n\u2022 `Formative Assessment` with which I use strategies for assessing where students\nare in their learning process and using the results to adjust instruction.",
